erved. Models for composite mergers predict\nabundance pattern dissimilar to those determined for the C-rich stars.\n[CW83]0904-02, though, may be a candidate for a composite He-WD merger, as it\nrotates and is more massive than the other stars. New evolutionary models for\nthe hot flasher scenario predict abundance patterns similar to those determined\nfor the C-rich stars. Hence, C-rich He-sdO may result from late He flashes with\ndeep-mixing episodes. (abbreviated)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Oct 2018 14:34:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-05"}
