re of the learned generative process, one can `invert' the learned\ngenerative model to perform unsupervised instance segmentation. On the\nchallenging CLEVR dataset, it is shown how our approach is able to improve over\nother recent purely unsupervised object-centric approaches to image generation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Oct 2018 20:17:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 Dec 2019 10:38:57 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 24 Jul 2020 13:10:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-27"}
